    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in Bind, where sending a flood of dynamic DNS updates may cause named to allocate large amounts of memory. This issue may cause named to exit due to a lack of free memory, resulting in a denial of service (DoS). \n            STATEMENT: The scope of this vulnerability is limited to trusted clients who are permitted to make dynamic zone changes.",
